From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 09 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: bump OpenCVGenPkgconfig minimum version to 3.5

OpenCVGenPkgconfig.cmake is invoked as a cmake -P script during the
build phase. CMake 4.0 removed compatibility with cmake_minimum_required
< 3.5, so the script aborts with an error before generating opencv4.pc.
Bump the version requirement to 3.5 to match CMake 4.0+ requirements.
---
 cmake/OpenCVGenPkgconfig.cmake | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/cmake/OpenCVGenPkgconfig.cmake b/cmake/OpenCVGenPkgconfig.cmake
--- a/cmake/OpenCVGenPkgconfig.cmake
+++ b/cmake/OpenCVGenPkgconfig.cmake
@@ -113,1 +113,1 @@
-cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 2.8.12.2)
+cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.5)
